title: Chris Alan - "Gotta Be Honest" | Full Comedy Special
description:
#standupcomedy #standup #comedy 

Hey everyone, it's Chris Alan!

I’m beyond excited to share my very first comedy special, *Gotta Be Honest*!  I’m super proud of it, and I can’t wait for you all to watch. It’s full of laughs and real moments about my life as a vet, a husband, and a dad. Trust me, it’s funny, it’s real, it’s ME!

Filmed in my hometown of Rochester, NY at Comedy at the Carlson, this special is a labor of love. If you enjoy it, feel free to show ya boy some love:

Venmo: @chrisalancomedy  
Cash App: $chrisjones1980  

Thanks so much for your support! I hope y'all love it as much as I loved making it! 

Produced by Mark Normand
Directed by Matt Peters
Edited by Gotham Production Studios

description:
#comedy #standup #marknormand 

The full special can be seen right here on Mark Normand's YouTube channel at 8pm Eastern on October 2nd!

In his debut comedy special *"Gotta Be Honest"*, Chris Alan delivers a fresh, hilarious take on life’s most relatable moments. From the ups and downs of family life to the chaos of relationships and the unpredictable journey of raising kids, Chris fearlessly dives into it all with his signature wit and charm. Produced by comedy veteran Mark Normand and directed by Matt Peters, the special captures the raw, unfiltered humor that has made Chris a rising star in the comedy scene.

Shot and edited by Gotham Production Studios, "Gotta Be Honest" brings Chris’s unique perspective to life with sharp comedic timing and storytelling that leaves no subject untouched. This debut special is packed with laugh-out-loud moments, offering a genuine look at the everyday struggles and absurdities of life, while showing why Chris Alan is a comedian to watch.

title: Andrew Youngblood: I'll Tell You This Full Comedy Special
description:
Thanks for tuning in!  This special is self-produced! So, your support is greatly appreciated. 
Please share my special anywhere you can & $$$ VENMO: @ybbooks Cashapp : $ybbooks

Mark Normand Presents ANDREW YOUNGBLOOD "I’ll Tell You This!"
Directed by JON CONNER https://www.instagram.com/jonconnerhtx?igsh=azUyZDg0NXU2ZjQy
FILMED BY  INSTAGRAM https://www.instagram.com/blueprintfilmco/

These are the best ways to support Andrew:
SUBSCRIBE to my YouTube channel @Noyoungblood 
LIKE, COMMENT, and SHARE this special to everyone you know!
COME SEE A LIVE SHOW: this site includes videos, tour dates, and more: www.andrewyoungblood.com

INSTAGRAM  https://www.instagram.com/noyoungblood
TikTok https://www.tiktok.com/@noyoungblood69?_t=8l2pl0QlOI7&_r=1
FACEBOOK https://www.facebook.com/andrew.youngblood.3/
TWITTER https://twitter.com/noyoungblood?lang=en

CHECK OUT MY PODCAST! 
THE MESS HALL WITH JAMIE AND ANDREW https://www.youtube.com/@UCQj-x3qlnxJ_sFfIJizEiHQ 
INSTAGRAM https://www.instagram.com/themesshallpod?igsh=MXNrNnhjOWNlOGNpdg%3D%3D

Thank you from the bottom of my heart for watching my debut special! 

Andrew Youngblood is a dark comedian who hails from upstate New York. Currently based in Texas, he travels all over the country, bringing his unique and twisted brand of humor to audiences everywhere. Andrew has been described as equal parts hilarious and disturbing, delivering punchlines that are sure to leave you laughing (and maybe a little disturbed). When he's not performing stand-up, Andrew co-hosts the podcast The Mess Hall with Jamie Rowan, where the two hosts completely Unqualified advice. Andrew's ability to find humor in the weirdest situations is on full display in the podcast, which has gained a loyal following online. Andrew opens for Mark Normand on tour and has worked with many comedians, including TJ Miller, Jenny Zigrino, Daniel Van Kirk, Sean Patton, and many more. His dark sense of humor is not for the faint of heart, but for those willing to take the plunge.

title: Doug Key: Mother Of The Year - Full Comedy Special
description:
Mark Normand Presents: Doug Key: “Mother of the Year” 
Filmed live at Comedy Connection in East Providence, Rhode Island. 
#Comedy #ComedySpecial #DougKey

Hey! It’s me, Doug Key! Thanks for watching my first-hour comedy special, where I reflect on my origin story as a child of divorced, alcoholic parents and irreverently dissect other interesting societal norms like modern dating, medical technology, and missing person posters. It’s a real coming-of-age tale. 

If you’d like to donate:
VENMO: @DougKeyComedy
PayPal: DougKeyComedy@gmail.com 

Follow me on socials!
Instagram: https://instagram.com/dougkeycomedy?igshid=OGQ5ZDc2ODk2ZA==
YouTube: https://youtube.com/@dougkeycomedy?si=b7is37tdhu8l4gYL
TikTok: https://www.tiktok.com/@dougkeycomedy?_t=8gb5KU0YNfn&_r=1
Facebook: https://www.facebook.com/profile.php?id=100087556373069&mibextid=LQQJ4d 

Written and Performed by: Doug Key 
Directed by: Jason Katz and Ryan Devir (@2buffoons )
Produced by: Cory Brailsford and Dave Fiorillo 
Edited by: Ryan Devir 
Audio and album services by: Ghost Runner Records 

Download the audio version here:  https://album.link/dougkey

Huge thank you to one of my oldest and best friends in comedy, Mark Normand, for presenting this special. Comedy!

For booking inquiries, email DougKeyComedy@gmail.com and check out 
www.DougKeyComedy.com for all info on shows, merch, and other stuff! 

Lastly, don’t forget to Check Your Fluids.

title: Mark Normand 'Soup to Nuts' OFFICIAL NETFLIX TRAILER
description:
“Soup to Nuts” out on Netflix 7/25 fatties!!! It’s a doozy. Give it a whirl, folks. Comedy!
#marknormand #comedy #netflixisajoke 

In Mark’s 5th hour, we cover everything from A to Queef, top to power bottom, soup to nuts. 

Special Directed By James Webb
Edit and Voiceover by Jason Katz  @2buffoons 
Thumbnail photo by Matthew Salacuse

Don't forget to subscribe.
Marknormandcomedy.com
TikTok - https://www.tiktok.com/@marknormandcomedy?lang=en
Instagram - https://www.instagram.com/marknormand/?hl=en
Twitter - @marknormand 

Mark Normand is a fun-loving New York comedian. Ok, I’m gonna brag a little here, but hey, you’re on the site, so that must mean you’re somewhat interested. I don’t know, I’ve just seen other comics do this. Ah, screw you, I’m proud of these credits! Sorry, I got worked up there. (I just wanna be liked)

So far, Mark has done a One-Hour Comedy Central special, “Don’t Be Yourself,” a Comedy Central HALF-HOUR special, has appeared on TBS’s CONAN 6 times,  Tonight Show with Jimmy Fallon, Late Show with Stephen Colbert, Showtime’s “Live at SXSW”, INSIDE AMY SCHUMER, TruTv, Best Week Ever, MTV, Last Comic Standing, @Midnight and released an album with Comedy Central records titled “Still Got It” (it’s not bad). Mark took first place at the Great American Comedy Festival competition this year. In 2013 won Caroline’s March Madness competition, beating out 63 other comedians. And this is a real shocker for all of us, but he was also voted Village Voice’s “Best Comedian of 2013”, I know, right? In 2012, Mark appeared on “John Oliver’s New York Standup Show” on Comedy Central, and in 2011 was picked as one of Comedy Central’s “Comics to Watch.”

Mark was born and raised in New Orleans, LA, surprisingly, to two normal parents. As a kid, he spent most of his time shooting short films and wetting the bed. He started doing comedy right after college and quickly moved to New York. Mark now does comedy clubs and colleges across the country and has been involved in many festivals, including Portland, Seattle, DC, Boston, Vancouver, and Melbourne and in 2013 was featured as a New Face at the Montreal Comedy Festival.

More annoying accolades that no one really cares about: Mark was named one of Comedy Central’s Comics To Watch for the 2011 New York Comedy Festival. Mark was also named Esquire’s “Best New Comedians 2012”, Splitsider’s “Top 10 Up and Coming Comedians on Each Coast”, and Time Out New York’s “21 New York Comedy Scene Linchpins”. Whew, sorry about all that.

title: Mark Normand presents MATT RUBY: SUBSTANCE (2023) - FULL SPECIAL 🌿🥃🍄🚫
description:
In this unique standup special, @MattRuby performs on weed, booze, 🍄🍄🍄, and sober. Presented by Mark Normand. More from Matt Ruby: https://www.youtube.com/mattruby

⭐️⭐️⭐️
Contribute:
• Venmo: @rubymatt
• Paypal: https://www.paypal.me/rubyisagem 
• SUPER THANKS on YouTube (it's above to the right of SHARE) 
⭐️⭐️⭐️

🚨 Message from MARK NORMAND: Matt Ruby is a helluva comic and ya gotta check out this special/doc where he performs high, drunk, sober, and tripping on shr👀ms. He's a good egg and I'm putting it here on my channel so even more folks get to see it. Get ready for some hilarious and magical moments – and I even pop up for some stoop zingers along the way. Comedy! 

▶️ New here? Watch/subscribe to Mark's YouTube channel:
https://www.youtube.com/marknormand

🚨 Message from MATT RUBY: Thanks Mark! First up, if you dig this special and want more, check out my stuff at the links below...

▶️ Watch/subscribe to Matt Ruby's YouTube channel: https://www.youtube.com/mattruby

📰 Subscribe to Matt Ruby's comedy newsletter, The Rubesletter:
https://mattruby.substack.com/

👨‍💻 Matt Ruby's comedy site:
https://mattrubycomedy.com/

Now, about the special...Phew, I really went for it. But like my friend Gina said, "It makes sense because you've done your 10,000 hours in comedy AND each one of these substances." True! It was a real adventure and got a bit sticky at points (screw you, booze!), but I'm grateful that people are finding it funny and interesting. Big props to director Matt Salacuse and editor Anthony Verderame for making it really sing. 
 
"Substance" was filmed at @NewYorkComedyClub and you can catch Mark and I there every Wednesday at our Good Eggs show. FYI, these weren’t typical special tapings where the audience gets all pumped up, they were just regular spots and the crowd didn’t know anything about what I was doing until I went onstage. The whole idea was an experiment to see what would happen if I performed outside my comfort zone: Would I crash and burn or could I still stick the landing? 🏍😬

More from Matt Ruby:

Mark Normand is a fun-loving, New York comedian. Ok, I’m gonna brag a little here but hey, you’re on the site so that must mean you’re somewhat interested. I don’t know, I’ve just seen other comics do this. Ah screw you, I’m proud of these credits! Sorry, I got worked up there. (I just wanna be liked)

So far, Mark has done a One-Hour Comedy Central special “Don’t Be Yourself”, a Comedy Central HALF HOUR special, has appeared on TBS’s CONAN 6 times,  Tonight Show with Jimmy Fallon, Late Show with Stephen Colbert, Showtime’s “Live at SXSW”, INSIDE AMY SCHUMER, TruTv, Best Week Ever, MTv, Last Comic Standing, @Midnight and released an album with Comedy Central records titled “Still Got It” (it’s not bad). This year, Mark took first place at the Great American Comedy Festival competition. In 2013 won Caroline’s March Madness competition, beating out 63 other comedians. And this is a real shocker for all of us, but he was also voted Village Voice’s “Best Comedian of 2013”, I know, right? In 2012, Mark appeared on “John Oliver’s New York Standup Show” on Comedy Central, and in 2011 was picked as one of Comedy Central’s “Comics to Watch.”

Mark was born and raised in New Orleans, LA surprisingly to two normal parents. As a kid he spent most of his time shooting short films and wetting the bed. He started doing comedy right after college and quickly moved to New York. Mark now does comedy clubs and colleges across the country and has been involved in many festivals including Portland, Seattle, DC, Boston, Vancouver, Melbourne and in 2013 was featured as a New Face at the Montreal Comedy Festival.

More annoying accolades that no one really cares about: Mark was named one of Comedy Central’s Comics To Watch for the 2011 New York Comedy Festival. Mark was also named Esquire’s “Best New Comedians 2012”, Splitsider’s “Top 10 Up and Coming Comedians on Each Coast”, and Time Out New York’s “21 New York Comedy Scene Linchpins”. Whew, sorry about all that.


#MarkNormand #StandupComedy #OutTolunch
